              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Be-8 spectrum from the reaction C-12(C-12,4-Be-8)O-16",
                "and alpha spectrum from the reaction C-12(C-12,a)Ne-20",
                "at bombarding energy of 65-MeV was represented."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Two surface barrier detector",
                "telescopes were set up at 8- and 12-degrees,",
                "respectively to the beam for particle identification of",
                "the reaction products. The telescope at 12-degree was",
                "for be-8 detection, which consist of del'Ta-e-e",
                "detectors of 43-mum and 2-mm and was set at a distance",
                "of 10.8-cm subtending solid angle of 8.15-msr with",
                "angular acceptance of +-2.9-degree at the target. The",
                "telescope at 8-degree consist of del'Ta-e-e detectors",
                "of 46.8-mum and 2-mm, respectively. It was at distance",
                "of 15.9-cm from target subtending solid angle of",
                " 1.1-msr and with angular acceptance of +-0.7-degree."
              ]
            }
          ],
